<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>JIRA does not currently have a formatter for PHP code. For example, the following block:</p>

<pre class="literal">
</pre><pre class="highlight"><code>
&lt;?php
    echo "Hello world!";
?&gt;
</code></pre>


<p>generates an error:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
&lt;?php
    echo "Hello world!";
?&gt;
</code></pre>

<p>A workaround is to omit the language parameter to the {``` block, but this falls back to Java syntax highlighting.</p>

    </div>
